[30;1m1703 | [0m[35mIn this case, substitution of `s` with `jomega` is not valid to obtain[0m
[30;1m1704 | [0m[35mthe Fourier transform.  This is because the poles of `Z` are not in[0m
[30;1m1705 | [0m[35mthe RH plane (they are on the imaginary axis and thus the system is[0m
[30;1m1706 | [0m[35mmarginally stable) and thus the evaluation of `Z(s)` at `s = jomega`[0m
[30;1m1707 | [0m[35mis outside the region of convergence of the Laplace transform.[0m
[30;1m1708 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m10 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m11 | [0m[35mLcapy is a Python package for symbolic linear circuit analysis and[0m
[30;1m12 | [0m[35msignal processing.  It can also simulate circuits using numerical[0m
[30;1m13 | [0m[35mintegration.  Lcapy can only symbolically analyse linear, time[0m
[30;1m14 | [0m[35minvariant networks.  In other words, networks comprised of basic[0m
[30;1m15 | [0m[35mcircuit components (R, L, C, etc.) that do not vary with time.[0m
[30;1m16 | [0m[35mHowever, changes in circuit topology (e.g., switching circuits) can be[0m
[30;1m17 | [0m[35manalysed as a sequence of initial value problems.[0m

[30;1m712 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m713 | [0m[35mLcapy's state-space analysis currently does not support degenerate[0m
[30;1m714 | [0m[35mcircuits.  These are circuits with a loop consisting only of voltage[0m
[30;1m715 | [0m[35msources and/or capacitors, or a cut set consisting only of current[0m
[30;1m716 | [0m[35msources and/or inductors.  In these cases, choosing capacitor voltages[0m
[30;1m717 | [0m[35m(or inductor currents) for the state variables produces dependent[0m
[30;1m718 | [0m[35mstate variables.[0m
